  A database schema is a conceptual representation of the structure of a database, including the tables, columns, and relationships between them. It defines the logical organization of the data and how it is stored and retrieved. The schema is used to design and plan the database, and it serves as a blueprint for the database's physical implementation. It is typically created before the actual database is built and is used to guide the design of the database's tables and their relationships. The schema is also used to ensure that the database meets the requirements of the application that will use it.
